<section id="about">
    <h2>About Us</h2>
    <p>The WitikaLab (NanoBioMat D3) is dedicated to researching and developing innovative nano(bio)materials such as nanofibers and nanocrystals. Our work aims to address a range of health challenges, including infectious, non-communicable, and chronic diseases.</p>
</section>

<section id="research">
    <h2>Research</h2>
    <p>Our research focuses on creating cutting-edge nano(bio)materials that have potential applications in diagnosing, treating, and managing various diseases. We are particularly interested in developing materials that can be used for infectious, non-communicable, and chronic diseases.</p>
</section>

